Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Roughly chop the @olives{1%sachet}.

Roughly chop the @tomatoes{2}.

In a #bowl{}, toss together olives, tomato and @chorizo{90%grams}. Season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Halve your @ciabatta{2%units}. Pop onto a lined #baking tray{} (cut-side up).

Spread the @sun dried tomato paste{2%sachets} over the bread.

Top with the chorizo mix and scatter over the @grated cheese{50%grams}.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese has melted and the edges are starting to crisp, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked carefully remove the topped ciabatta from the oven.

Pop onto a #sharing board{} and cut into small triangles.